      <h3 class="title">Burning Pandaren Spirit - Townlong Steeps (57.0, 42.2)</h3>
      <div class="story">
        <p> This fight is an odd thinking with the Firespirit pet of the tamer. The pet
          will cast a spell with a debuff, I used to block that but after thinking about it
          I tried to time out the big hit and block that and just take the dot. I found that
          this way was abit faster.
          If this strat is not good for you there is a
          Wowhead link at the bottom, so you cant comb through the other strats.
        </p>
        <h4 class="title">The Pets</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Idol (1,2,1)</li>
          <li>Carry</li>
          <li>Emerald Proto-Whelp (2,2,1)</li>

          <p>Once again there is some AOE here some use a mid-level pet</p>
          <p>If you use the same team as the last fight it will be 25 here!!!</p>
        </ul>
        <h4 class="title">The Strat</h4>
        <br />
        <h6 class="title">Crimson</h6>
        <p>
        <ul>
          <li>Crush</li>
          <li>Stoneskin</li>
          <li>Deflect</li>
          <li>Crush to win</li>
        </ul>
        </p>
        <h6 class="title">Firespirit</h6>
        <p>
        <ul>
          <li>Deflect - Pets conflagrate is a 4 round CD(one more round than Deflect)</li>
          <li>Stoneskin - trainers pet will heal here</li>
          <li>Crush</li>
          <li> Save deflect for the conflag. Keep up Stoneskin. Crush as filler.
          Seems to me at least that the trainer sometimes won't cast conflag on CD.</li>
        </ul>
        </p>
        <h6 class="title">Glowy</h6>
        <p>
        <ul>
          <li>Glowy's first two moves are posions shots. Can Deflect or swap in the carry here.</li>
          <li>Swap in the carry at some point here</li>
          <li>Glow other than the two shots only stampeds so stoneskin or presence and attack to win</li>
        </ul>
        </p>
